      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I am Suncheng Xiang, a final-year PhD student at Shanghai Jiao Tong University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before this, I graduated from Changsha University of Science &amp;amp; Technology (CSUST) for B.Eng in Electrical Engineering and Automation in 2014, then obtained the M.Eng from National University of Defense Technology (NUDT) in 2017.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My main research topics are computer vision and machine learning. Specifically, I am currently doing research works on person re-identification, domain adaptation, transfer learning and related applications. I am also interested in some image generation and image retrieval tasks, e.g. vehicle re-identification and fine-grained image retrieval tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
